                <objectIdentifier xml:id="MoP">
                    <msName>The March of Progress</msName>
                </objectIdentifier>
                <note>The short story "March of Progress" was published in <hi rend="italic">The Century</hi> in 1901, and it features a dramaticization of the problem facing a black schoolboard in Patesville, North Carolina in the 1880s (William L. Andrews, <hi rend="italic">The Literary Career of Charles W. Chesnutt</hi>, Louisiana State University Press, 1999: 82).</note>
            </object>
            
            <object type="magazine">
                <objectIdentifier xml:id="tc">
                    <msName>The Century</msName>
                </objectIdentifier>
                <note><hi rend="italic">The Century Magazine</hi> was an American magazine published by The Century Company that replaced <hi rend="italic">Scribner's Monthly Magazine</hi> in 1881. The magazine published illustrated articles on history, science, and literature, sometimes publishing fiction as well. In 1930, it merged with <hi rend="italic">The Forum</hi>.</note>
            </object>
        </listObject>
        
